Now, the `fixed_code`: We need to provide the corrected version of the `getLine` function. The bug is in the final condition. The fix: after finding that there is no newline from pos, we should check if pos < js.length() and return js.substring(pos) (the rest of the line) otherwise return null. So the fixed function should be:

```java
public String getLine(int lineNumber) {
    String js = "";
    try {
      js = getCode();
    } catch (IOException e) {
      return null;
    }

    int pos = 0;
    int startLine = 1;

    if (lineNumber >= lastLine) {
      pos = lastOffset;
      startLine = lastLine;
    }

    for (int n = startLine; n < lineNumber; n++) {
      int nextpos = js.indexOf('\n', pos);
      if (nextpos == -1) {
        return null;
      }
      pos = nextpos + 1;
    }

    lastOffset = pos;
    lastLine = lineNumber;

    int nextNewline = js.indexOf('\n', pos);
    if (nextNewline == -1) {
      // If no more newline, return the rest of the string if there is content,
      // otherwise null.
      if (pos < js.length()) {
        return js.substring(pos);
      } else {
        return null;
      }
    } else {
      return js.substring(pos, nextNewline);
    }
}
```

